        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Carus was preparing the German translation of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> (Carus trans. 1871).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had changed the reference from ‘Mr. Algen’ to ‘Dr. Chapman’ (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_887.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Algernon Chapman</ref>) in the second printing of <hi rend="italic">Descent.</hi></note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD had cited <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3026.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Lubbock’s</ref> <hi rend="italic">Pre-historic times</hi>, which used the spelling ‘Feegeans’ (Lubbock 1869, pp. 445–6; see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 1: 77 n. 10). The spelling was changed to ‘Fijians’ in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1967.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. 102.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6144.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Louis Leguay</ref>. In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1967.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, index, the spelling was corrected to Leguay.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">This was corrected in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1967.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. 510.</note>
        </div>        
            
